<!-- 6: PRACTICE -->
<!-- SECTION: Practice Zone -->
<section id="practice" class="c6">
  <h2 class="sec-title"><span class="tab-num">6</span>Practice Zone</h2>
  <p>Time to put it all together! These activities revisit Elena and Diego's conversation and the language you've just studied — work through them at your own pace, and check your answers as you go.</p>

  <h3 style="color:var(--gold);">6.1 — True or False: Comprehension Check</h3>
  <div id="tf-quiz"></div>
  <div class="score-track" id="tf-score"></div>

  <h3 style="color:var(--gold);">6.2 — Match the Country to the Nationality</h3>
  <div class="match-grid" id="match-game"></div>
  <div class="score-track" id="match-score"></div>

  <h3 style="color:var(--gold);">6.3 — Multiple Choice: Grammar Check</h3>
  <div id="mc-quiz"></div>

  <h3 style="color:var(--gold);">6.4 — Fill in the Blank</h3>
  <p style="font-size:14px;">Complete each sentence. Then click "Check answers".</p>
  <div class="box" style="padding:16px 20px;">
    <p>1. <span class="fill-blank"><input data-answer="I'm" placeholder="I'm/you're"></span> Elena. (I am)</p>
    <p>2. <span class="fill-blank"><input data-answer="are" placeholder="am/is/are"></span> you from Mexico? (question)</p>
    <p>3. She <span class="fill-blank"><input data-answer="is" placeholder="am/is/are"></span> happy today.</p>
    <p>4. I <span class="fill-blank"><input data-answer="'ve" placeholder="'ve/'s"></span> got two brothers. (I have)</p>
    <p>5. He <span class="fill-blank"><input data-answer="'s" placeholder="'ve/'s"></span> got one sister. (he has)</p>
    <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="checkFillBlanks()">Check answers</button>
    <div id="fill-feedback" class="score-track"></div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 7: ERROR CLINIC -->
<!-- SECTION: Error Clinic -->
<section id="errorclinic" class="c7">
  <h2 class="sec-title"><span class="tab-num">7</span>Error Clinic</h2>
  <p>Even careful learners make small mistakes with "to be" and "have got" when they're new to English. Here are five sentences a student might write — read each one. Some have mistakes — fix them. <b>One sentence is already correct — do not "fix" it if it isn't broken.</b></p>
  <div class="box" style="padding:16px 20px;">
    <ol style="font-size:14.5px;">
      <li>"I are from Poland." <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block'">Reveal</button><div class="reveal-content">Incorrect — "I" needs "am": "I <b>am</b> from Poland."</div></li>
      <li>"She have got two brothers." <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block'">Reveal</button><div class="reveal-content">Incorrect — "she" needs "has got": "She <b>has got</b> two brothers."</div></li>
      <li>"He is happy." <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block'">Reveal</button><div class="reveal-content"><b>This sentence is already correct — no error here.</b> "He" correctly takes "is". Resist the urge to change anything.</div></li>
      <li>"You is tired." <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block'">Reveal</button><div class="reveal-content">Incorrect — "you" needs "are": "You <b>are</b> tired."</div></li>
      <li>"I've got three children." <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.style.display='block'">Reveal</button><div class="reveal-content"><b>Also correct.</b> "I've got" correctly matches "I". A second trap — not every sentence needs a correction.</div></li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 8: WRITING -->
<!-- SECTION: Your Turn: Writing Task -->
<section id="writing" class="c8">
  <h2 class="sec-title"><span class="tab-num">8</span>Your Turn: Writing Task</h2>
  <p>Now it's your turn to do exactly what Elena and Diego did on their first day — introduce yourself in writing.</p>
  <p>Write <b>3–4 short sentences</b> (about <b>20–30 words</b>) about yourself. Say your name, where you're from, your nationality, and one feeling. Use "I'm" and "I've got" if you can.</p>
  <textarea class="writing-area" id="writing-box" placeholder="Start writing here..."></textarea>
  <div class="word-count" id="word-count">0 words</div>
  <div class="notice-q" style="margin-top:14px;"><b>Self-check before you submit:</b> Did you write "I'm" (not "I is")? Did you use a capital letter at the start of your name and country?</div>
</section>


<!-- SECTION: Speaking Practice -->
<section id="speaking">
  <h2 class="sec-title"><span class="tab-num" style="background:var(--blue)">&#128483;</span>Speaking Practice</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">This week you say hello, say your name, and say where you are from &mdash; out loud. Use the voice memo app on your phone. Speaking to your phone is easy practice!</p>

  <div class="speak-card">
    <span class="speak-type">My introduction</span>
    <h3>30 seconds: this is me</h3>
    <p>Say your introduction. Four sentences:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><em>"Hello! My name is&hellip;"</em></li>
      <li><em>"I'm from&hellip;"</em> (your country)</li>
      <li><em>"I live in&hellip;"</em> (your city)</li>
      <li><em>"Nice to meet you!"</em></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="speak-how"><strong>How:</strong> Record it. Listen. Record it again &mdash; a little faster and with a smile (you can hear a smile!). <strong>Check:</strong> <em>I'm</em> = "I am". Say it as ONE word: <em>"I'm from&hellip;"</em></div>
  </div>

  <div class="speak-card">
    <span class="speak-type">Roleplay: first meeting</span>
    <h3>Hello, what's your name?</h3>
    <p><strong>Person A</strong> asks: <em>"Hi! What's your name? Where are you from?"</em></p>
    <p><strong>Person B</strong> answers: <em>"I'm&hellip; I'm from&hellip; And you?"</em></p>
    <p>Then change! Person B asks, Person A answers.</p>
    <div class="speak-how"><strong>How:</strong> With a partner &mdash; or play both people yourself with two voices. Record 1&ndash;2 minutes. <strong>Check:</strong> <em>"And you?"</em> &mdash; two small words that keep every conversation alive. Did you use them?</div>
  </div>

  <div class="speak-card">
    <span class="speak-type">Shadowing drill</span>
    <h3>Copy the classroom phrases</h3>
    <p>Find the Classroom Language section in this unit. Choose 4 phrases (for example: <em>"Can you repeat that, please?" &mdash; "How do you spell it?"</em>). Read each one aloud <strong>three times</strong>: slowly &rarr; normal &rarr; friendly and natural.</p>
    <div class="speak-how"><strong>How:</strong> Record the third time. <strong>Check:</strong> questions go UP at the end &mdash; <em>"Can you repeat that? &#8599;"</em> These phrases are your tools for EVERY class. Learn them with your voice, not only your eyes.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tip-box">
    <h3>Tips for your first English words</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Say your introduction every day in front of the mirror. 30 seconds. After one week, it comes out by itself.</li>
      <li>Speak slowly. Slow and clear is GOOD English.</li>
      <li>Practise spelling your name aloud: <em>"M-A-R-I-A."</em> People will ask you &mdash; be ready!</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>


