<!-- SECTION: Speaking Practice -->
<section id="speaking">
  <h2 class="sec-title"><span class="tab-num" style="background:var(--blue)">&#128483;</span>Speaking Practice</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">Who's this? This week you describe people &mdash; family, friends, photos &mdash; with your voice. Voice memo app ready!</p>

  <div class="speak-card">
    <span class="speak-type">Describe a person</span>
    <h3>45 seconds: someone I love</h3>
    <p>Open a photo of a family member or friend on your phone. Describe the person in <strong>about 45 seconds</strong>:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Who is it? <em>"This is my sister."</em></li>
      <li>What is she like? <em>"She's tall. She's funny."</em></li>
      <li>One more thing: <em>"She's 25. She's a teacher."</em></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="speak-how"><strong>How:</strong> Look at the photo and record. <strong>Check:</strong> <em>He's / She's</em> = "he is / she is". One smooth word.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="speak-card">
    <span class="speak-type">Sentence challenge</span>
    <h3>Six words and their opposites</h3>
    <p>Say one sentence with each pair &mdash; about real people (no names needed!). Up to <strong>60 seconds each</strong>:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><em>tall / short</em></li>
      <li><em>young / old</em></li>
      <li><em>funny</em></li>
      <li><em>strong</em></li>
      <li><em>beautiful / handsome</em></li>
      <li><em>thin / big</em></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="speak-how"><strong>How:</strong> One recording, timer on. <strong>Check:</strong> the adjective does NOT change &mdash; <em>"They are tall,"</em> never "talls."</div>
  </div>

  <div class="speak-card">
    <span class="speak-type">Roleplay: who's this?</span>
    <h3>The photo game</h3>
    <p><strong>Person A</strong> shows a photo (family, friends, or famous people) and asks: <em>"Who's this?"</em></p>
    <p><strong>Person B</strong> answers or guesses: <em>"Is it your brother? He's very tall!"</em> Then change roles.</p>
    <div class="speak-how"><strong>How:</strong> Best with a partner &mdash; alone, describe three photos and record. <strong>Check:</strong> <em>Who's</em> = "who is". Same music as <em>he's, she's, it's.</em></div>
  </div>

  <div class="tip-box">
    <h3>Tips: describing people kindly</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Start with who, then two adjectives, then one fact. Small recipe, complete description.</li>
      <li>Describe people in photos on your phone &mdash; one photo a day, three sentences. Free practice!</li>
      <li>Kind words first: <em>funny, friendly, smart.</em> They make every description warmer.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>


