    <h3>Six times, out loud</h3>
    <p>Say these times from YOUR day &mdash; full sentences: <em>"I get up at seven o'clock. My class is at half past six."</em> Up to <strong>60 seconds each</strong>:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>When you get up</li>
      <li>When you have lunch</li>
      <li>When your English class starts</li>
      <li>When you have dinner</li>
      <li>When you go to bed</li>
      <li>The time RIGHT NOW (look at a clock!)</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="speak-how"><strong>How:</strong> One recording, timer on. <strong>Check:</strong> <em>"It's seven o'clock. It's half past two."</em> The time always starts with <em>It's&hellip;</em></div>
  </div>

  <div class="speak-card">
    <span class="speak-type">Roleplay: this and that</span>
    <h3>What's this? What are those?</h3>
    <p>Walk around your room. Point at things near you and far from you:</p>
