      <li><em>a book &rarr; books</em></li>
      <li><em>a bag &rarr; bags</em></li>
      <li><em>a phone &rarr; phones</em></li>
      <li><em>a chair &rarr; chairs</em></li>
      <li><em>a key &rarr; keys</em></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="speak-how"><strong>How:</strong> One recording, timer on. <strong>Check the -s sound:</strong> <em>books</em> = "s", <em>pens/bags</em> = "z". Small sound, big difference &mdash; listen for it!</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tip-box">
    <h3>Tips: times and things</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Say the time aloud every time you look at a clock this week. Ten times a day, free practice.</li>
      <li>Touch and talk: touching real things while naming them builds strong memory.</li>
      <li>Numbers first! If big times are hard, practise 1&ndash;12 aloud until they are automatic.</li>
