<!-- SECTION: Speaking Practice -->
<section id="speaking">
  <h2 class="sec-title"><span class="tab-num" style="background:var(--blue)">&#128483;</span>Speaking Practice</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">It's the goodbye party! This week your voice learns the music of greetings, small talk, and goodbyes &mdash; the sentences you will use for the rest of your English life. Voice memo app ready!</p>

  <div class="speak-card">
    <span class="speak-type">Roleplay: at the party</span>
    <h3>Hello &rarr; talk &rarr; goodbye</h3>
    <p>Play a small party conversation, start to finish:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Hello:</strong> <em>"Hi! How are you?" &mdash; "I'm great, thanks! And you?"</em></li>
      <li><strong>Talk:</strong> ask two questions you know: <em>"Where are you from? What do you do? Do you like the music?"</em></li>
      <li><strong>Goodbye:</strong> <em>"It was nice talking to you! Take care &mdash; see you soon!"</em></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="speak-how"><strong>How:</strong> With a partner, or both people yourself. Record 2 minutes. <strong>Check:</strong> a real conversation has three parts &mdash; hello, talk, goodbye. Did yours have all three?</div>
  </div>

  <div class="speak-card">
    <span class="speak-type">Shadowing drill</span>
    <h3>The greetings melody</h3>
    <p>Choose 5 greetings from this week's list (<em>"Good morning!" &mdash; "Nice to meet you!" &mdash; "Take care!"</em>). Say each one aloud <strong>three times</strong>: slowly &rarr; normal &rarr; warm and real, like you mean it.</p>
    <div class="speak-how"><strong>How:</strong> Record the third time. <strong>Check the melody:</strong> greetings go UP and smile &mdash; <em>"Good MORning! &#8599;"</em> A flat greeting sounds sad. Warm voice, warm welcome.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="speak-card">
    <span class="speak-type">My little speech</span>
    <h3>30 seconds: thank you and goodbye</h3>
    <p>Imagine: it's the last day of this course. Make a tiny goodbye speech &mdash; <strong>30 seconds</strong>:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><em>"Thank you, everyone!"</em></li>
      <li>One thing you learned: <em>"Now I can talk about my job!"</em></li>
      <li><em>"Good luck &mdash; and see you soon!"</em></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="speak-how"><strong>How:</strong> Record it &mdash; then listen to your very first recording from Week 1. Hear the difference? That's five weeks of your voice growing. Keep both recordings!</div>
  </div>

  <div class="tip-box">
    <h3>Tips: keep speaking after the party</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Greet someone in English every day &mdash; a friend, your mirror, your phone. Greetings are muscles: use them.</li>
      <li>Learn goodbye pairs: <em>"See you soon!" &mdash; "Take care!"</em> One says it, one answers it.</li>
      <li>Your 30-second introduction + your 30-second goodbye = your first real English conversation. You have both now!</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>


